name: BMO High Quality Corporate Bond Index ETF
longDescription: The ETF seeks to replicate, to the extent possible, the performance of an investment grade corporate bond index, net of expenses. Currently, the ETF seeks to replicate the performance of the FTSE Canada 1-10 year A+ Corporate Bond Index (the Index). The investment strategy of the ETF is to invest in and hold the constituent securities in the same proportion as they are reflected in the Index. The Manager may also use a sampling methodology in selecting investments for the ETF. As an alternative to or in conjunction with investing in the constituent securities of the Index, the ETF may invest in or use Other Securities (as defined in the prospectus) to obtain exposure to the performance of the Index.
